# React: Sorting Articles

## Description
Article listing and sorting application built with React. The user can sort the articles by number of upvotes or by publication date.

## Requirements
- *Node.js 8 LTS or higher*
- [Download & Install Node.JS](https://nodejs.org/)

## Installation
```bash
npm install
```

## How to Run
```bash
npm start
```

## How to Test
```bash
npm test
```

## Features
- Displays articles in a table when the application starts
- By default, articles are sorted by *upvotes in descending order*
- *Most Upvoted* button: re-sorts the articles by number of upvotes (descending)
- *Most Recent* button: re-sorts the articles by publication date (descending)

## Data Structure
Each article is an object with the following properties:

| Property | Type   | Description                              |
|----------|--------|-------------------------------------------|
| title    | string | Article title                             |
| upvotes  | number | Number of upvotes the article has         |
| date     | string | Publication date in YYYY-MM-DD format     |

## Main Files
- `src/App.js` — Main component with sorting logic
- `src/components/Articles.js` — Article table component

## Test Attributes (data-testid)
| Element                        | data-testid        |
|---------------------------------|---------------------|
| Most Upvoted button             | `most-upvoted-link` |
| Most Recent button              | `most-recent-link`  |
| Each article row (`<tr>`)       | `article`           |
| Article title (`<td>`)          | `article-title`     |
| Article upvotes (`<td>`)        | `article-upvotes`   |
| Article date (`<td>`)           | `article-date`      |
